Three people have died in an accident involving a minibus taxi and a truck on the N3, near Estcourt, on Thursday morning. KwaZulu Natal Emergency Medical Services (KZN EMS), Robert Mckenzie said paramedics treated 12 people on the scene, including a child. He appealed to motorists to adhere to the traffic laws and "please be extremely cautious on the road as we're experiencing high traffic volumes". The police are investigating a case of culpable homicide. 